WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:06.120
Chapter 12 of Proverbs. King James Version. This LibriVox recording is in the public domain.

00:06.740 --> 00:08.420
Recording by Michael Packard.

00:09.660 --> 00:12.200
Whoso loveth instruction loveth knowledge,

00:13.020 --> 00:15.860
but he that hateth reproof is brutish.

00:16.780 --> 00:19.240
A good man obtaineth favor of the Lord,

00:19.960 --> 00:22.780
but a man of wicked devices will he condemn.

00:24.480 --> 00:27.280
A man shall not be established by wickedness,

00:27.280 --> 00:30.780
but the root of the righteous shall not be moved.

00:31.940 --> 00:39.700
A virtuous woman is a crown to her husband, but she that maketh ashamed is as rottenness in his bones.

00:41.140 --> 00:46.060
The thoughts of the righteous are right, but the counsels of the wicked are deceit.

00:46.720 --> 00:52.740
The words of the wicked are to lie and wait for blood, but the mouth of the upright shall deliver them.

00:52.740 --> 00:57.980
The wicked are overthrown and are not, but the house of the righteous shall stand.

00:59.540 --> 01:05.800
A man shall be commended according to his wisdom, but he that is of a perverse heart shall be despised.

01:07.340 --> 01:14.280
He that is despised and hath a servant is better than he that honoreth himself and lacketh bread.

01:15.500 --> 01:21.580
A righteous man regardeth the life of the beast, but the tender mercies of the wicked are cruel.

01:23.560 --> 01:27.340
He that tilleth his land shall be satisfied with bread,

01:28.080 --> 01:31.620
but he that followeth vain persons is void of understanding.

01:32.900 --> 01:35.400
The wicked desireth the net of evil men,

01:36.140 --> 01:38.400
but the root of the righteous yieldeth fruit.

01:40.200 --> 01:43.380
The wicked is snared by the transgression of his lips,

01:44.020 --> 01:46.080
but the just shall come out of trouble.

01:46.080 --> 01:50.220
A man shall be satisfied with good by the fruit of his mouth,

01:50.720 --> 01:54.920
and the recompense of a man's hands shall be rendered unto him.

01:56.000 --> 01:58.500
The way of a fool is right in his own eyes,

01:59.080 --> 02:01.980
but he that hearkeneth unto counsel is wise.

02:02.620 --> 02:07.720
A fool's wrath is presently known, but a prudent man covereth shame.

02:09.200 --> 02:11.920
He that speaketh truth showeth forth righteousness,

02:12.860 --> 02:14.960
but a false witness deceit.

02:14.960 --> 02:18.640
There is that speaketh like the piercings of a sword,

02:19.700 --> 02:21.500
but the tongue of the wise is health.

02:22.940 --> 02:25.700
The lip of truth shall be established for ever,

02:26.300 --> 02:28.760
but a lying tongue is but for a moment.

02:30.100 --> 02:32.520
Deceit is in the heart of them that imagine evil,

02:33.120 --> 02:35.520
but to the counselors of peace is joy.

02:36.700 --> 02:39.100
There shall no evil happen to the just,

02:39.700 --> 02:42.160
but the wicked shall be filled with mischief.

02:42.840 --> 02:45.820
Lying lips are abomination to the Lord,

02:46.260 --> 02:48.840
but they that deal truly are his delight.

02:50.480 --> 02:52.640
A prudent man concealeth knowledge,

02:53.600 --> 02:56.260
but the heart of fools proclaimeth foolishness.

02:56.760 --> 02:59.200
The hand of the diligent shall bear rule,

02:59.920 --> 03:02.780
but the slothful shall be under tribute.

03:04.140 --> 03:06.920
Heaviness in the heart of man maketh it stoop,

03:08.040 --> 03:09.940
but a good word maketh it glad.

03:11.220 --> 03:14.360
The righteous is more excellent than his neighbor,

03:14.720 --> 03:17.100
but the way of the wicked seduceth them.

03:17.520 --> 03:21.160
The slothful man roasteth not that which he took in hunting,

03:21.800 --> 03:24.420
but the substance of a diligent man is precious.

03:24.800 --> 03:26.980
In the way of righteousness is life,

03:27.260 --> 03:30.020
and in the pathway thereof there is no death.

